content:
{
  "name": "@wetransfer/concorde",
  "version": "0.0.1",
  "description": "A sexy pinnacle of engineering that’s nonetheless incredibly inefficient and expensive and goes out of business because it can’t find enough use",
  "main": "index.js",
  "sideEffects": false,
  "scripts": {
    "bootstrap": "lerna bootstrap",
    "build": "lerna run build",
    "docs": "esdoc",
    "lint": "lerna run lint",
    "precommit": "sh scripts/git/pre_commit_hooks",
    "prepush": "sh scripts/git/pre_push_hooks",
    "test": "lerna run test",
    "test:ci": "npm run test:coverage -- --bail --runInBand --verbose=false && npm run test:codacy",
    "test:codacy": "cat ./coverage/lcov.info | ./node_modules/.bin/codacy-coverage && rm -rf ./coverage",
    "test:coverage": "jest --coverage",
    "test:watch": "jest --watch"
  },
  "repository": {
    "type": "git",
    "url": "git+https://github.com/WeTransfer/concorde.js.git"
  },
  "keywords": [
    "wetransfer"
  ],
  "author": "WeTransfer folks",
  "license": "MIT",
  "bugs": {
    "url": "https://github.com/WeTransfer/concorde.js/issues"
  },
  "homepage": "https://github.com/WeTransfer/concorde.js#readme",
  "devDependencies": {
    "@wetransfer/eslint-config-wetransfer": "1.2.1",
    "babel-preset-env": "1.6.1",
    "codacy-coverage": "2.0.3",
    "esdoc": "1.0.4",
    "esdoc-standard-plugin": "1.0.0",
    "eslint": "4.13.1",
    "husky": "0.14.3",
    "jest": "21.2.1",
    "lerna": "2.5.1",
    "prettier": "1.9.2",
    "rollup": "0.52.1",
    "rollup-plugin-babel": "3.0.2",
    "rollup-plugin-uglify": "2.0.1"
  },
  "jest": {
    "setupFiles": [
      "./scripts/jest/setup-environment.js"
    ]
  },
  "lint-staged": {
    "*.{js,json,md}": [
      "prettier --write",
      "git add"
    ]
  }
}
